text: Obiageli Olorunsola (born 11 May 1962) is a Nigerian badminton player. She competed in women's singles and mixed doubles at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:Nigerian female badminton players Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic badminton players of Nigeria Category:Badminton players at the 1994 Commonwealth Games Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for Nigeria
